    "summary": "Prof.dr.ir. Twan Basten is a Professor of Computational Models in the Department of Electrical Engineering at the Eindhoven University of Technology (TU/e) and a Research Fellow at the Embedded Systems Institute, both located in Eindhoven, the Netherlands. \n\nIn 1993, he received a Master's degree (with honors) in Computing Science from the TU/e, for a project on distributed debugging performed at the University of Waterloo, Ontario, Canada. In 1998, he received his PhD degree in Computing Science from the same university. Twan Basten worked as assistant and associate professor in Computer Science and Electrical Engineering at the TU/e, and as visiting researcher at Philips Research Laboratories and Carnegie Mellon University, Pittsburgh, PA. His current research interest  is the design of embedded and cyber-physical systems with a focus on networked and multiprocessor systems, design-space exploration and computational models. To obtain reliable systems, their design should be model-driven and based on rigorous mathematical foundations.  Twan Basten has served (or is serving) in over 60 technical program committees. He was the Ambient Intelligence co-chair in the DATE 2003 TPC, topic chair in the DATE 2004 and 2005 TPCs, the TPC co-chair for ACSD 2007, TPC chair of MoCC 2008, special session co-chair in the DSD 2012 TPC, and special session chair in the DSD 2013 TPC. He (co)authored 1 book and more than 250 scientific publications, of which seven received a best paper award. He (co)supervised over 20 PhD degrees. He is a senior member of the IEEE and a life member of the ACM.\n\nSpecialties: Computational Models, Embedded Systems, Cyber-Physical Systems, Model-driven Design, Performance Engineering",
